BEGIN:VEVENT
IMAGE;VALUE=URI;DISPLAY=BADGE;FMTTYPE=image/webp:https://houstonheights.org
 /wp-content/uploads/2026/01/Great-American-Pie-Contest-2026-flyer.webp
ATTACH;FMTTYPE=image/webp:https://houstonheights.org/wp-content/uploads/202
 6/01/Great-American-Pie-Contest-2026-flyer.webp
UID:aa28iBvXRhhfVDly51QMn
SUMMARY:July 2026 General Meeting
DTSTAMP:20260626T013118Z
DTSTART:20260713T183000Z
DESCRIPTION:Mark your calendars! The Houston Heights Association’s Great Am
	erican Pie Contest is coming to our General Meeting on Monday\, July 13 at
	 6:30 PM. \nThink your pie recipe is the best in the Heights? Enter one of
	 our four categories: \n\n\nSweet \n\n\nSavory \n\n\nJunior Baker \n\n\nPr
	esentation \n\n\nContestants are required to enter 2 pies for judging\, an
	d a panel of 6 judges will decide who takes home bragging rights as the He
	ights’ top pie baker of 2026. Prizes will be awarded for 1st\, 2nd\, and 3
	rd place in each category. There will also be a Best Presentation Award\, 
	selected by People’s Choice\, so be sure to bring your creativity along wi
	th your baking skills! \nWhether you’re baking or just cheering on your ne
	ighbors\, everyone is invited to join the fun. Bring your appetite and you
	r community spirit—we can’t wait to see you there! \n\nSUBMIT YOUR PIE\n\n
	https://houstonheights.org/event/july-2026-general-meeting/\n\nFrom Housto
	n Heights Association
URL:https://houstonheights.org/event/july-2026-general-meeting/
LOCATION:Houston Heights City Hall & Fire Station\, 107 W. 12th Street\, Ho
	uston\, TX\, 77008\, United States
X-CALRIPPER-SOURCE:houston-heights-association
CATEGORIES:Houston Heights Association
TRANSP:TRANSPARENT
DURATION:PT2H
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
IMAGE;VALUE=URI;DISPLAY=BADGE;FMTTYPE=image/png:https://hmh.org/wp-content/
 uploads/Elementary-720-x-440-px.png
ATTACH;FMTTYPE=image/png:https://hmh.org/wp-content/uploads/Elementary-720-
 x-440-px.png
UID:CijC_s60BAqVgl-TIygKW
SUMMARY:Introduction to Teaching the Holocaust
DTSTAMP:20260626T013118Z
DTSTART:20260714T090000Z
DESCRIPTION:Join Holocaust Museum Houston for a one day workshop designed t
	o help educators to feel comfortable teaching about the Holocaust. The day
	 will include a tour of the museum’s Holocaust Gallery\, a talk from a Hol
	ocaust survivor or descendant\, best practices for teaching about the Holo
	caust\, an overview of some of the free resources available\, and more.  \
	nBreakfast and lunch will be provided. \nTeachers will earn 6 CPE hours an
	d 6 GT update hours. \nTeachers from the 6th-12th grade\, in all subject a
	reas\, are encouraged to participate in this FREE workshop. Sign up throug
	h the registration link below. \nIf you have any questions about the works
	hop\, contact us as education@hmh.org.    \nInterested in a more in-depth 
	exploration of the Holocaust? We also offer the Max M. Kaplan Summer Insti
	tute for Educators\, which includes pedagogical and content sessions from 
	scholars and museum educators. You can find more information and apply her
	e: https://hmh.org/education/professional-development/max-m-kaplan-summer-
	institute/. \n			\n				Register Here\n\nhttps://hmh.org/event/introduction
	-to-teaching-the-holocaust/\n\nFrom Holocaust Museum Houston
URL:https://hmh.org/event/introduction-to-teaching-the-holocaust/
LOCATION:Holocaust Museum Houston Classroom
X-CALRIPPER-SOURCE:holocaust-museum-houston
CATEGORIES:Holocaust Museum Houston
TRANSP:TRANSPARENT
DURATION:PT7H
END:VEVENT
